FT  05 MAY 92 / Construction Contracts: Council housing
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Contracts totalling more than Pounds 6m have been awarded to WIMPEY
CONSTRUCTION MIDLANDS by Birmingham City Council and Wolverhampton Borough
Council.
A Pounds 4.1m contract comprises jobbing repairs, cyclical maintenance and
minor improvements to the Wolverhampton Borough Council's leisure, social
and educational building stock.
On the Overpool Estate in Ward End, Birmingham, work is being carried out
worth Pounds 800,000 to provide 31 families with totally rewired, replumbed,
redecorated and centrally heated accommodation.
