<HEADLINE>
FT  05 MAY 92 / Management (The Growing Business): Taking all the factors
into account - In A Nutshell
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Association of British Factors &amp; Discounters reported a 12 per cent
increase in the volume of client companies' turnover in the first quarter of
1992 compared with the same period of last year.
The turnover of association members rose to Pounds 3.75bn from Pounds 3.34bn
reflecting both an increase in the number of companies using the services of
members and growth in the turnover of existing clients.
The association, whose members provide cash to their clients against
invoices, said the increase was a sign that small and medium-sized
businesses were starting to recover from the recession.
</TEXT>
