<HEADLINE>
FT  05 MAY 92 / Management (The Growing Business): Investment trust
completes fund - In A Nutshell
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Candover Investments, a listed investment trust which finances management
buy-outs and development capital projects, has completed fund-raising for
its Candover 1991 Fund with Pounds 37.5m of money raised.
When it launched the new fund, which will back buy-outs and buy-ins valued
at up to Pounds 5m, last September, Candover set a target of between Pounds
30m and Pounds 60m.
A tough fund-raising climate has prevented several recent funds from
reaching the top of their target range.
The new fund succeeds a Pounds 30m fund raised in 1987 also intended for
smaller investments and now fully invested.
</TEXT>
