NUCPS civil-service union said it would recommend that members reject the
offer, worth 4.5 per cent on the pay bill.
A significant minority of staff would receive only the 4.1 per cent
cost-of-living element. Most would receive around 4.4 per cent, including
performance-related pay.
The substantial rises for 1,000 civil servants - all executive officers at
the bottom of their grades, earning between Pounds 7,854 and Pounds 8,180 -
include compensation for loss of annual increases guaranteed under the
current pay structure.
The union will debate whether to call for an industrial action ballot,
including strikes, at its conference on May 12.
</TEXT>
