</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   LOS ANGELES
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
A week before the King trial decision, another verdict that caused outrage
and protests among members of the city's black community was upheld by an
appeals court, Louise Kehoe reports from Los Angeles. The convicted killer
of a young black woman was sentenced to probation instead of jail. A
15-year-old black girl argued with a Korean grocer over a bottle of orange
juice. As the girl left the store the grocer shot her in the back of the
head.
