FT  02 MAY 92 / How To Spend It: A cut-price trove of solid silver bounty
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LUCIA VAN DER POST
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   IF YOU are looking for a present
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
whether for a wedding, a christening, a birthday or an anniversary - it is
worth taking a look at the mail-order company Silver Direct.
A selection of its silverware is pictured below. Nothing it sells is
startling. You will not find in its brochure anything to amaze or wonder at.
What you will find is solid, dependable, classic (if not staid) pieces at
very affordable prices. Silver Direct sells fine-quality silver made into
the sort of everyday articles that most people want at prices that it claims
are considerably lower than most retailers - and a quick check reveals its
claims to be true.
For example, some admirably plain cutlery - Rat Tail design - selling at
Pounds 50 for a place setting (table knife, fork, spoon, desert knife, fork
and spoon) in silver-plate and at Pounds 238 a place-setting in sterling
silver sells in another emporium for Pounds 107 for silver plate and Pounds
354 for sterling silver. Other classic patterns - Old English, Kings,
Queens, Fiddle Thread and Shell, Albany, Dubarry and St. James - are also
available.
Then there are hip flasks (Pounds 185) and pillboxes (Pounds 45), a plain
square silver-plated photograph frame (3 1/3 ins by 2 1/2 ins Pounds 16),
silver and gilt 12 bore salt and pepper shakers (Pounds 129), pure bristle
silver military bushes and combs (Pounds 165) and all the other
appurtenances deemed essential to the solid bourgeois life.
On the more glamorous front there is also a selection of jewellery - safe
and accessible as you would expect (Russian bangles, twisted knot ear-rings)
but nonetheless good value. Nothing in the brochure costs more than Pounds
500.
Part of the reason prices are good is that Silver Direct does not hold a lot
of stock, so orders take between one week and a month to arrive. The other
reason is that Silver Direct has low overheads, no city centre rents and few
staff. For a brochure write to Silver Direct, 3 Crosland Place, Taybridge
Road, London SW11 5PJ. Tel: 071-228-0634.
