<HEADLINE>
FT  02 MAY 92 / Briefcase, Q&amp;A: What can I pay my wife?
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
WHAT is the maximum weekly amount which I could pay my wife for assistance
in my business for the last tax year without having to pay National
Insurance stamps.
The weekly exemption limit for wages actually paid in 1991-92 was Pounds
51.99; the corresponding limit for the current tax year (1992-93) is Pounds
53.99.
(Class 1 NIC is no longer collected bu means of stamps.)
